---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base title="About — Pauls Workshop" description="About Paul: AI Administrator and Microsoft 365 / Azure solution builder.">
  <section class="hero" style="padding-bottom: 24px;">
    <div class="wrap">
      <p class="eyebrow">about</p>
      <h1>Hello, I'm Paul.</h1>
      <p class="lede muted">
        I build things on Microsoft 365, Copilot, and Azure — and I document what I build here.
        My background is enterprise Microsoft 365 developer come administration; my present is
        building AI agent solutions on Copilot and Azure — and writing about
        it as I go.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section" style="border-top: none; padding-top: 12px;">
    <div class="wrap" style="max-width: 720px; margin: 0 auto;">
      <h2>What this site is</h2>
      <p>
        This is my workshop, open to visitors. 
        I've spent years in enterprise Microsoft 365 environments, and these days my focus is AI agents and Azure.
        The articles here are my working notes made public: agent experiments, licensing and cost models, 
        Retrieval API explorations, governance setups — written down while the details are still fresh.
      </p>

      <h2>What I write about</h2>
      <p>
        Copilot agent building (declarative and custom engine), agent licensing
        and the Copilot Credits model, the Retrieval API, Copilot Studio, the
        Microsoft 365 Agents SDK, Azure AI Foundry, and the governance side:
        Entra Agent ID, Purview, and Defender.
      </p>

      <h2>The work behind the words</h2>
      <p>
        Everything here traces back to something real — a personal lab in my own environment, 
        an experiment that finally worked, a problem I actually hit and solved. 
        The portfolio page shows the builds; the articles show the thinking.
      </p>

      <h2>Contributors</h2>
      <p>
        This site also publishes articles from invited contributors — friends
        and colleagues building in the same space. Every article carries its
        author's byline. If you'd like to write here, get in touch.
      </p>

      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>
        The fastest ways to reach me are
        <a href="https://ae.linkedin.com/in/paul-ignatius-francis-4b36a057" rel="me">LinkedIn</a> or
        <a href="mailto:paulignatius@outlook.com">email</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
